In England, in the seven days to 29 September, there were 192,058 new confirmed cases (339.6 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 22 September, there were 177,798 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 8% (14,260 extra cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 04 October is 6,752,536 (11,940.8 cases per 100,000 population).
